Text: Well done, everyone.
Mmph...!
Lady Eta. Unfortunately, time is up.

Ngh... There goes my chance to increase the budget
and personnel...

You were really fighting with that end in mind,
weren't you? Honestly...

Lady Eta, please release Lady Gamma from your slime
control.

We will hold a meeting to discuss the insights
obtained from this training.
Huff...huff...! M-My body...is exhausted...!

Oh, she's back to being clumsy again. Were Gamma's
nimble movements just a fluke?

Yeah...that went well. I can control her basic
movements without any issues...

Nghh... Even if I can move gracefully, it doesn't
mean anything if I can't move by my own free will!

...I've summarized the training details based on the
hypothetical scenario of "A Surprise Attack from
Within the Ancient City"!

The scenario assumes that our defense system has
been disabled for some reason, allowing an invasion
to reach the doorstep of Alexandria's core!

That's impossible... No one can get through my
defense system.

There are always exceptions to everything. Even you
were surprised by my movements today, weren't you?
Grr...

Including the defensive actions of the Shadow Garden
members, the reduction in defensive strength in this
case is about 40%.

It is reasonable to assume that Alexandria's actual
defensive capability largely depends on Lady Eta's
defense system.

Adding around 200 permanent combatants would
provide coverage in emergencies, but it remains
an unreliable measure.

Given that the discovery of the possessed is
inherently irregular, increasing the number of
combatants is essentially a supplementary measure.

While time might resolve this issue, there's also
the possibility that it will never be resolved.

Bringing in external defense forces is out of the
question. That said, it's not as if all the Seven
Shadows are always in Alexandria...
Lady Gamma is right. So, I have a proposal—
...Not happening.
Lambda hasn't said anything yet.

I know what Lambda's gonna say next... That the
Seven Shadows who are always in the ancient city
should take command of the defense.

Yes! Since you reside in Alexandria, Lady Eta, if
you were to be our Defense Commander, it would
significantly enhance our defensive capabilities!

Not happening...! Research and experimentation take
priority over everything...!

If we need a Defense Commander, Lambda...
you can do it.

Well...! While I could take on that role, it would
hinder my training of new recruits!

In that case...delegate the training to someone
else.

But taking command of training new recruits isn't
something just anyone can pick up immediately...!

Same here. My research and experiments can only be
done by me.

...If you increase the budget and personnel, I could
create a defense system...that will never be
disabled.

Even if I were to grant you that permission, you
would squander the Garden's budget like there's no
tomorrow, wouldn't you?

Of course, that's the plan. The Garden's budget
exists for research and experimentation.

No, it doesn't! It absolutely doesn't! At least, not
just for that!

It's not something we can decide immediately,
including whether or not we should appoint a
dedicated Defense Commander.

Let's continue discussing how to address the defense
issues of the ancient city revealed during this
training session.
...I want money.
That's something everyone wants, Eta.

If only I had the budget...everything would go
smoothly. It would solve so many problems...
Master Shadow, you think so too...right?
Well...I'm not so sure about that...

(Defense training in Alexandria, and all the budget
issues surrounding that...)

(No matter how Eta puts it, this is essentially a
ruthless war over allowances among the Seven
Shadows...!)

(Unfortunately, I have no choice but to remain
completely neutral in this war waged by these
girls.)

(After all, even I'm struggling because the Kagenou
family's allowance is far from sufficient!)

(...Lately, the number of bandits in the territory
seems to be decreasing. There's a high chance that I
over-hunted them.)

I thought bandits would just naturally spring up,
but...maybe that's not the case...?!

Hey, Master Shadow. Do you have any Shadow
Wisdom on how to make...more money?

...Eta, are you really thinking of using your brains
to make money over research and experiments?

But without money, I can't conduct research or
experiments.

...Yeah, you have a point! Even a shadowbroker needs
resources first!
So, do you have any ideas...?
Hmm, let's see...

Well, for a poor aristocrat like me, it would be
tough due to my position, but...how about acquiring
land and flipping it?
Land... You mean, real estate...?

Exactly. Increase the value of the land, sell it for
a high price, and then use that money to buy other
valuable land—
...Whoaaa.
(...But simply explaining it is a futile exercise.)

(Besides, it's not like such land is just lying
around. If it did exist, it would have become
someone else's property a long time ago.)

(Ultimately, even to buy land, you need a decent 
amount of money upfront to take the plunge.)

(That's right. Just because this is a different world,
doesn't mean there are a ton of convenient
opportunities where you can create something from
nothing!)

Ack... Losing the white truffle gathering site was a
heavy blow. That's a 100 million zeni loss per hill...!
...Alright.

Thank you, Master Shadow... I'll find land, flip
it...and raise the necessary budget.
Great! Good luck, Eta!
...Heheheh...
